race.comment: Former Victorian EYE OF THE EAGLE (3) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this assignment easier than what he faced down south. Tuned up for this with two recent trials and any push in betting must be respected. BOLD JULIUS (2) is a consistent conveyance who has placed two from two over this course and distance and gets 2kg off from the inside marble. Plenty to like about his prospects. STANISLAUS (4) has a solid record over this six-furlong journey only missing a drum once in five starts. Shapes as one to consider. BEWS (1) was a touch disappointing last time out but the form prior was good enough for a race of this nature. Worth another chance. GIVING DELIGHT (9) best of the rest.
